==English==
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg|breeder}}

#A person who [[breed]]s animals professionally
#(''gay slang; derogatory'') A [[heterosexual]]; i.e. one whose sexual intercourse can lead to [[breeding]]
#A type of [[nuclear reactor]] that creates material suitable for the production of atomic weapons.  (See Wikipedia's article on [[w:fast breeder|fast breeder reactor]]s.)
#(''slang, derogatory'') a person who has had or who is capable of having children; a person who is focussed on the rearing of their own children
#:'''Quotations:'''
#:*1729:"The number of souls in this kingdom being usually reckoned one million and a half, of these I calculate there may be about two hundred thousand couple whose wives are '''breeders'''; from which number I subtract thirty thousand couples who are able to maintain their own children, although I apprehend there cannot be so many, under the present distresses of the kingdom; but this being granted, there will remain an hundred and seventy thousand '''breeders'''." &mdash; [[w:Jonathan Swift|Jonathan Swift]] ''[[s:A Modest Proposal|A Modest Proposal]]''
#:'''Usage note:''' This meaning is generally either an ironic usage (as in the Swift quotation) or an intentionally offensive usage (by implying that parenthood is the same as animal husbandry).
